( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:01:36,100 --> 00:01:40,800
[EP9: Hopeless Unrequited Crush]

2
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:06,640
Look at me.

3
00:02:06,640 --> 00:02:09,120
Why are you avoiding me?

4
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:13,080
Hello, is this the
Linyuan District Police Station?

5
00:02:13,080 --> 00:02:16,899
We met a flasher
in the alley near Su City No.1 High School.

6
00:02:19,439 --> 00:02:22,506
Miss, just now...

7
00:02:22,506 --> 00:02:23,800
This alley isn't safe.

8
00:02:23,800 --> 00:02:24,840
Don't walk through here anymore.

9
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:26,353
Okay.

10
00:02:26,353 --> 00:02:28,200
Come with me. It's alright.

11
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:29,360
Come on.

12
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:31,160
Let's go.

13
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:37,925
Alright, we've got the situation.

14
00:02:37,925 --> 00:02:40,920
We'll arrange for the relevant personnel
to install surveillance cameras.

15
00:02:40,920 --> 00:02:43,160
But installing them
will take some coordination.

16
00:02:43,160 --> 00:02:45,000
Earliest would be tomorrow.

17
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:47,053
- Thank you so much.
- You're welcome.

18
00:02:52,260 --> 00:02:56,100
[Notice: Flasher seen nearby. Stay alert.
This is a crime. You will be prosecuted.]

19
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:46,039
Ruan Yu?

20
00:03:46,039 --> 00:03:48,100
Lawyer Xu?

21
00:03:53,586 --> 00:03:54,879
Are you okay?

22
00:03:54,879 --> 00:03:56,739
I'm fine.

23
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:09,381
- What are you doing in Su City?
- What are you doing in Su City?

24
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:15,000
My mom and I

25
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:17,080
came back to clean up the old house

26
00:04:17,080 --> 00:04:19,173
and pack our things.

27
00:04:20,040 --> 00:04:21,524
Lawyer Xu,

28
00:04:21,524 --> 00:04:24,440
are you here to visit your family?

29
00:04:24,440 --> 00:04:25,953
Yes.

30
00:04:27,320 --> 00:04:30,946
Then why did you go there just now?

31
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:35,399
I was just passing by.

32
00:04:35,399 --> 00:04:36,800
I heard something happened,

33
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:39,040
so I came to check it out.

34
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:41,720
<i>He's also here for this matter.</i>

35
00:04:52,440 --> 00:04:54,780
Is this all you're having for dinner?

36
00:04:55,520 --> 00:04:57,700
I don't have much of an appetite.

37
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:04,760
Were you scared just now?

38
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:08,546
Yes.

39
00:05:10,760 --> 00:05:12,760
Since you were scared,

40
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:15,100
why did you still do it?

41
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:22,759
So that people who walk that path

42
00:05:22,759 --> 00:05:25,633
will no longer be afraid.

43
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:35,240
But next time,

44
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:37,279
if something like this happens again,

45
00:05:37,279 --> 00:05:39,139
you should...

46
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:43,040
Stay out of it?

47
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:44,400
Find someone

48
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:47,686
to help you with it.

49
00:06:03,280 --> 00:06:05,640
These two...

50
00:06:05,640 --> 00:06:08,640
Didn't they both say they couldn't remember?

51
00:06:08,640 --> 00:06:10,640
But they don't look like...

52
00:06:10,640 --> 00:06:13,460
they've just met.

53
00:06:17,760 --> 00:06:19,661
<i>Hello, sir.</i>

54
00:06:20,840 --> 00:06:22,880
<i>Young man, it's you!</i>

55
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:25,560
<i>What a coincidence! That girl...</i>

56
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:27,672
<i>That one...</i>

57
00:06:27,672 --> 00:06:29,620
<i>She came! Do you remember her?</i>

58
00:06:29,620 --> 00:06:30,960
<i>- I don't.
- You...</i>

59
00:06:30,960 --> 00:06:33,040
<i>Go ahead with your work. I'll read for a while.</i>

60
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:34,813
<i>Wait...</i>

61
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:40,600
<i>You don't remember, and she doesn't either.</i>

62
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:42,240
<i>So I'm the only one here...</i>

63
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:44,220
<i>getting all excited for nothing?</i>

64
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:51,786
Looks like they still have a long way to go.

65
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:12,381
Like going to the police station
and ask for help.

66
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:19,439
<i>What were you thinking, Ruan Yu?</i>

67
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:20,600
<i>Wake up!</i>

68
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:22,079
<i>It's Xu Huai Song, okay?</i>

69
00:07:22,079 --> 00:07:24,259
<i>This isn't some romantic comedy.</i>

70
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:29,760
This afternoon,

71
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:32,479
I already talked to the police.

72
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:40,780
Why did you come to No.1 High School today?

73
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:46,759
I was just wandering around,

74
00:07:46,759 --> 00:07:49,439
and I ended up here.

75
00:07:49,439 --> 00:07:50,439
So...

76
00:07:50,439 --> 00:07:51,480
Lawyer Xu,

77
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:54,479
why aren't you spending the day
with your family?

78
00:07:56,440 --> 00:07:58,819
I don't usually celebrate these dates.

79
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:02,000
That makes sense.

80
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:04,860
Foreign countries don't have
the 24 Solar Terms like we do.

81
00:08:08,639 --> 00:08:10,699
Lawyer Xu.

82
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:13,577
Did you go abroad

83
00:08:13,577 --> 00:08:16,036
right after graduating from high school?

84
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:24,000
Back then,

85
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:27,100
why did you choose to study abroad?

86
00:08:31,440 --> 00:08:33,500
Family arrangements.

87
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:38,573
It wasn't your own choice?

88
00:08:39,440 --> 00:08:42,221
Then did you want to go abroad?

89
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:48,760
I suppose it was my choice too.

90
00:08:48,760 --> 00:08:50,820
But if...

91
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:02,379
There are no "ifs."

92
00:09:15,280 --> 00:09:16,799
It's getting late.

93
00:09:16,799 --> 00:09:19,059
When are you going back to Hang City?

94
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:23,040
I'll stay at the old house for the night.

95
00:09:23,040 --> 00:09:25,200
Once that matter is fully resolved tomorrow,

96
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:27,080
I'll go back.

97
00:09:28,919 --> 00:09:30,480
I can give you a ride in a bit.

98
00:09:30,480 --> 00:09:32,920
No, thanks. You don't have to do this.

99
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:35,019
Safety first.

100
00:09:53,038 --> 00:09:54,960
<i>Family arrangements.</i>

101
00:09:54,960 --> 00:09:57,480
<i>I told you a long time ago,</i>

102
00:09:57,480 --> 00:09:58,904
<i>I don't have a son.</i>

103
00:09:58,904 --> 00:10:01,600
<i>If you want to go, go by yourself.</i>

104
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:03,400
<i>Liar.</i>

105
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:05,380
<i>Mom.</i>

106
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:11,039
It seems he and his mom

107
00:10:11,039 --> 00:10:13,420
don't really get along.

108
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:18,326
Did his family send him abroad

109
00:10:21,560 --> 00:10:24,120
for some other reason?

110
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:26,320
<i>I suppose it was my choice too.</i>

111
00:10:26,320 --> 00:10:28,459
<i>But if...</i>

112
00:10:34,760 --> 00:10:36,700
<i>There are no "ifs."</i>

113
00:10:41,120 --> 00:10:43,200
Forget it.

114
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:45,880
There are no "ifs" anyway.

115
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:47,600
What's the point...

116
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:49,900
of dwelling on this?

117
00:11:08,120 --> 00:11:10,960
<i>Su City female college student murder case...</i>

118
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:13,399
<i>Suspect acquitted,</i>

119
00:11:13,399 --> 00:11:17,300
<i>victim's family begs for justice in tears.</i>

120
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:19,640
<i>Stop.</i>

121
00:11:19,640 --> 00:11:22,560
[Murderer]
<i>Stop. Go back and do your homework.</i>

122
00:11:28,799 --> 00:11:32,559
<i>Even if you clean them all today,
there will be more tomorrow.</i>

123
00:11:32,559 --> 00:11:33,559
<i>I'll just paint</i>

124
00:11:33,559 --> 00:11:35,800
<i>the wall red later.</i>

125
00:11:35,800 --> 00:11:37,399
<i>If you insist on handling this case,</i>

126
00:11:37,399 --> 00:11:39,200
<i>don't ever come back!</i>

127
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:42,080
<i>You're completely unreasonable.</i>

128
00:11:56,040 --> 00:11:59,060
<i>It wasn't your own choice?</i>

129
00:11:59,680 --> 00:12:02,620
<i>Then did you want to go abroad?</i>

130
00:12:30,520 --> 00:12:33,440
It's raining so heavily again.

131
00:12:34,720 --> 00:12:37,461
I hope I'm not stuck here again today.

132
00:12:40,039 --> 00:12:42,620
Why is no one taking the order?

133
00:13:01,679 --> 00:13:03,559
Ruan Yu! It's really you!

134
00:13:03,559 --> 00:13:04,919
What are you doing here?

135
00:13:04,919 --> 00:13:07,080
<i>Why do I keep running into these two siblings?</i>

136
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:09,720
I'm heading to the high-speed rail station.

137
00:13:09,720 --> 00:13:11,960
- High-speed rail station?
- Yes.

138
00:13:11,960 --> 00:13:13,320
We're going the same way.

139
00:13:13,320 --> 00:13:15,639
Why don't you get in? We can give you a ride.

140
00:13:15,639 --> 00:13:17,639
No, thanks. I'm hailing a ride.

141
00:13:17,639 --> 00:13:19,200
The driver should be here soon.

142
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:22,400
It's pouring out there. Just get in!

143
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:27,639
I can't park here for long. Get in.

144
00:13:27,639 --> 00:13:29,540
Thank you.

145
00:13:36,840 --> 00:13:38,960
Just put it anywhere.

146
00:13:38,960 --> 00:13:40,920
Sorry for the trouble.

147
00:13:40,920 --> 00:13:43,400
Seatbelt.

148
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:44,519
Song,

149
00:13:44,519 --> 00:13:45,960
in novels, the gentleman hero

150
00:13:45,960 --> 00:13:48,360
always helps the heroine fasten her seatbelt.

151
00:13:48,360 --> 00:13:51,160
No need. I can do it myself.

152
00:13:54,640 --> 00:13:56,461
Thanks.

153
00:14:01,756 --> 00:14:03,159
It's the weekend.

154
00:14:03,159 --> 00:14:05,780
What are you doing near the school again?

155
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:08,640
We went to the supermarket.

156
00:14:08,640 --> 00:14:11,760
My brother said
there's been a pervert near the school lately

157
00:14:11,760 --> 00:14:12,919
and told me to avoid that area,

158
00:14:12,919 --> 00:14:15,660
so he brought me here to learn the route.

159
00:14:17,120 --> 00:14:18,480
Even though the guy was caught,

160
00:14:18,480 --> 00:14:20,320
we still have to take precautions.

161
00:14:20,320 --> 00:14:21,440
Yes.

162
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:24,600
<i>So he drove back and forth,</i>

163
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:27,279
<i>"taking precautions" for a whole hour,</i>

164
00:14:27,279 --> 00:14:29,880
<i>until the person he was waiting
for finally showed up.</i>

165
00:14:29,880 --> 00:14:33,720
<i>The Xu siblings have really been through a lot.</i>

166
00:14:33,720 --> 00:14:35,200
I'll take her home first.

167
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:37,236
Then we'll head straight back to Hang City.

168
00:14:37,236 --> 00:14:38,457
Okay.

169
00:14:38,457 --> 00:14:39,519
Lawyer Xu,

170
00:14:39,519 --> 00:14:41,240
are you also going back?

171
00:14:41,240 --> 00:14:42,797
Yes.

172
00:14:46,800 --> 00:14:49,580
[Refund Confirmation Su City - Hang City]

173
00:14:56,040 --> 00:14:57,559
<i>Talk to her, Song!</i>

174
00:14:57,559 --> 00:14:59,000
<i>Say something!</i>

175
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:01,159
<i>Ruan Yu likes cool guys,</i>

176
00:15:01,159 --> 00:15:03,973
<i>not mute guys, okay?</i>

177
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:09,000
<i>You're usually so eloquent,</i>

178
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:10,120
<i>but at critical moments like this,</i>

179
00:15:10,120 --> 00:15:12,780
<i>I'm the one who has to break the ice.</i>

180
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:15,320
Ruan Yu.

181
00:15:15,320 --> 00:15:18,280
Did you come to our school yesterday?

182
00:15:18,280 --> 00:15:20,280
Yes.

183
00:15:20,280 --> 00:15:23,240
Zhao Da told me that a writer

184
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:24,360
came to our school yesterday.

185
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:26,159
He saw her while playing soccer.

186
00:15:26,159 --> 00:15:28,200
It was you, right?

187
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:30,099
Zhao Da?

188
00:15:32,880 --> 00:15:34,240
<i>What's your name?</i>

189
00:15:34,240 --> 00:15:35,880
<i>Zhao Yi.</i>

190
00:15:35,880 --> 00:15:38,386
<i>"Yi" with a "cart" radical, not "iron."</i>

191
00:15:38,386 --> 00:15:40,320
<i>Zhao Yi.</i>

192
00:15:40,320 --> 00:15:43,080
<i>So, he's actually Xu Huai Shi's classmate.</i>

193
00:15:43,080 --> 00:15:45,540
<i>Luckily, I didn't say much.</i>

194
00:15:46,919 --> 00:15:50,099
I just happened to be wandering around there.

195
00:15:51,080 --> 00:15:54,240
But I don't think our school allows loitering.

196
00:15:54,240 --> 00:15:57,219
Ruan Yu, how did you get in?

197
00:15:58,840 --> 00:16:00,780
I...

198
00:16:01,720 --> 00:16:03,520
Maybe the security guard
wasn't paying attention,

199
00:16:03,520 --> 00:16:06,640
or maybe he just thought I looked trustworthy.

200
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:09,520
<i>That was a seamless lie.</i>

201
00:16:09,520 --> 00:16:12,800
<i>No wonder my brother
can't find a way to confess.</i>

202
00:16:14,840 --> 00:16:17,240
Ruan Yu, you already went to No.1 High School,

203
00:16:17,240 --> 00:16:20,360
so why didn't you come see me?

204
00:16:20,360 --> 00:16:23,560
Xu Huai Shi,
do you think everyone is as free as you?

205
00:16:23,560 --> 00:16:25,280
If you're so desperate to talk,

206
00:16:25,280 --> 00:16:27,440
you can recite your textbooks.

207
00:16:36,200 --> 00:16:37,279
Ruan Yu!

208
00:16:37,279 --> 00:16:40,326
Where did you get that canvas bag?

209
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:43,840
A friend gave it to me.

210
00:16:43,840 --> 00:16:46,639
How did you know such an amazing friend?

211
00:16:46,639 --> 00:16:48,799
This is the same canvas bag that Shi Can has.

212
00:16:48,799 --> 00:16:52,179
He often carries it when he's at events.

213
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:56,520
Are you a fan of Li Shi Can?

214
00:16:56,520 --> 00:16:57,586
Yes.

215
00:16:57,586 --> 00:16:59,000
I remember this canvas bag

216
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:01,159
is a commemorative limited edition.

217
00:17:01,159 --> 00:17:03,320
Ruan Yu, what kind of friend is this?

218
00:17:03,320 --> 00:17:04,359
That's so cool!

219
00:17:04,359 --> 00:17:05,759
Xu Huai Shi.

220
00:17:05,759 --> 00:17:06,799
Ruan Yu,

221
00:17:06,799 --> 00:17:09,039
are you also a fan of Shi Can?

222
00:17:09,039 --> 00:17:10,359
Do you have some special connection?

223
00:17:10,359 --> 00:17:11,450
Can you share it with me?

224
00:17:11,450 --> 00:17:13,559
Xu Huai Shi, is this what you study

225
00:17:13,559 --> 00:17:15,400
all day at school?

226
00:17:15,400 --> 00:17:17,040
It doesn't affect my studies.

227
00:17:17,040 --> 00:17:19,079
- What are you...
- Yes. A little star-chasing now and then

228
00:17:19,079 --> 00:17:20,400
is a good way to rest and recharge.

229
00:17:20,400 --> 00:17:21,600
Besides,

230
00:17:21,600 --> 00:17:22,800
Li Shi Can

231
00:17:22,800 --> 00:17:25,284
is a positive idol, right?

232
00:17:25,284 --> 00:17:26,440
Exactly!

233
00:17:26,440 --> 00:17:28,960
And Shi Can is incredibly positive

234
00:17:28,960 --> 00:17:31,039
both in his work and in his personal life.

235
00:17:31,039 --> 00:17:32,079
He has so much energy,

236
00:17:32,079 --> 00:17:35,000
and he brings his fans positive vibes.

237
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:37,120
Even Ruan Yu is attracted to him.

238
00:17:37,120 --> 00:17:40,320
Song, I told you I had good taste.

239
00:17:40,320 --> 00:17:41,960
He's really excellent.

240
00:17:41,960 --> 00:17:45,400
I can learn a lot from him.

241
00:17:45,400 --> 00:17:49,060
That doesn't mean you can use
our family's money to support him.

242
00:17:51,753 --> 00:17:53,080
<i>No wonder Xu Huai Song</i>

243
00:17:53,080 --> 00:17:55,097
<i>is so hostile toward Li Shi Can.</i>

244
00:17:55,097 --> 00:17:57,540
<i>So, that's the reason.</i>

245
00:18:00,079 --> 00:18:01,520
We're almost there.

246
00:18:01,520 --> 00:18:04,686
Stop talking and get ready to get off.

247
00:18:21,766 --> 00:18:23,240
Be careful.

248
00:18:23,240 --> 00:18:25,760
It's pouring out there!

249
00:18:27,440 --> 00:18:29,560
Be careful.

250
00:18:29,560 --> 00:18:30,880
Bye, Ruan Yu!

251
00:18:30,880 --> 00:18:33,540
- Bye!
- Bye, Song!

252
00:19:19,720 --> 00:19:22,381
<i>It's Li Shi Can's song...</i>

253
00:19:34,039 --> 00:19:36,659
Have you started updating your novel again?

254
00:19:38,320 --> 00:19:40,340
Not yet.

255
00:19:41,640 --> 00:19:44,080
Are you still not ready,

256
00:19:44,080 --> 00:19:46,359
or is it a lack of inspiration?

257
00:19:46,359 --> 00:19:49,526
Probably because I haven't posted for too long,

258
00:19:49,526 --> 00:19:52,306
and now I can't pick up the thread.

259
00:19:58,000 --> 00:19:59,760
If you hadn't stopped,

260
00:19:59,760 --> 00:20:01,720
what was the original ending

261
00:20:01,720 --> 00:20:04,059
you planned for the novel?

262
00:20:06,480 --> 00:20:08,379
It was...

263
00:20:13,240 --> 00:20:15,840
It's about the hero and heroine

264
00:20:15,840 --> 00:20:18,240
going on a graduation trip

265
00:20:18,240 --> 00:20:20,240
after the college entrance exam.

266
00:20:29,840 --> 00:20:32,059
<i>Let me see.</i>

267
00:20:32,680 --> 00:20:35,200
<i>Ruan Yu, haven't you already signed up?</i>

268
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:38,180
<i>I just want to see who else is going.</i>

269
00:20:38,180 --> 00:20:40,780
[Class 10, Senior 3, Xu Huai Song]

270
00:20:41,680 --> 00:20:42,800
<i>Xiao Fei, your number.</i>

271
00:20:42,800 --> 00:20:45,240
<i>- Go ahead.
- 188...</i>

272
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:47,600
<i>- 2571...
- 188...</i>

273
00:20:47,600 --> 00:20:50,400
<i>He signed up too.</i>

274
00:20:52,840 --> 00:20:56,419
<i>Are you sure you're going to confess?</i>

275
00:20:57,080 --> 00:20:58,880
<i>Two classes traveling together,</i>

276
00:20:58,880 --> 00:21:01,640
<i>what a great opportunity.</i>

277
00:21:01,640 --> 00:21:03,520
<i>I don't care if he's planning to study abroad</i>

278
00:21:03,520 --> 00:21:05,320
<i>or if he likes someone else.</i>

279
00:21:05,320 --> 00:21:07,000
<i>As long as he's still single,</i>

280
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:10,173
<i>I'm 18 and I've got the right
to confess my feelings.</i>

281
00:21:10,173 --> 00:21:11,440
<i>I've thought it through.</i>

282
00:21:11,440 --> 00:21:13,680
<i>No matter the outcome,</i>

283
00:21:13,680 --> 00:21:15,359
<i>I have to give my youth</i>

284
00:21:15,359 --> 00:21:17,379
<i>a proper closure.</i>

285
00:21:29,400 --> 00:21:30,843
<i>Ruan Yu,</i>

286
00:21:30,843 --> 00:21:32,720
<i>over here!</i>

287
00:21:41,720 --> 00:21:44,680
<i>- Stop it!
- Stop looking. He's not here yet.</i>

288
00:21:44,680 --> 00:21:45,960
<i>He's not here?</i>

289
00:21:45,960 --> 00:21:48,560
<i>What gift did you choose for your confession?</i>

290
00:22:06,800 --> 00:22:08,400
<i>Why did you fold so many?</i>

291
00:22:08,400 --> 00:22:10,960
<i>They represent the 1,013 days
of our high school life.</i>

292
00:22:10,960 --> 00:22:13,200
<i>Not a single one can be missing.</i>

293
00:22:13,840 --> 00:22:15,317
<i>You spent over a week</i>

294
00:22:15,317 --> 00:22:17,200
<i>folding more than a thousand paper stars.</i>

295
00:22:17,200 --> 00:22:21,280
<i>That's the power of love.</i>

296
00:22:21,280 --> 00:22:23,526
<i>How do I look?</i>

297
00:22:25,360 --> 00:22:27,420
<i>Perfect.</i>

298
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:29,640
<i>What's taking him so long?</i>

299
00:22:29,640 --> 00:22:31,200
<i>- He should be here soon.
- Attention!</i>

300
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:32,880
<i>Everyone is here.</i>

301
00:22:32,880 --> 00:22:34,400
<i>Get on the bus.</i>

302
00:22:34,400 --> 00:22:37,240
<i>Monitor, is everyone here?</i>

303
00:22:37,240 --> 00:22:39,799
<i>Monitor, what about Xu Huai Song?</i>

304
00:22:39,799 --> 00:22:43,153
<i>- Xu Huai Song?
- Xu Huai Song from Class 10.</i>

305
00:22:44,200 --> 00:22:46,279
<i>Xu Huai Song isn't coming.</i>

306
00:22:46,279 --> 00:22:48,759
<i>He's probably not interested
in this kind of group activity.</i>

307
00:22:48,759 --> 00:22:50,546
<i>Zhou Jun, get on the bus.</i>

308
00:22:54,060 --> 00:22:55,240
<i>You two, hurry up!</i>

309
00:22:55,240 --> 00:22:56,480
<i>There are still seats in the front.</i>

310
00:22:56,480 --> 00:22:57,920
<i>- Hurry up!
- Okay.</i>

311
00:22:57,920 --> 00:22:59,319
<i>So...</i>

312
00:22:59,319 --> 00:23:01,160
<i>does he really have no attachment</i>

313
00:23:01,160 --> 00:23:03,400
<i>to anyone here at all?</i>

314
00:23:03,400 --> 00:23:05,539
<i>Maybe we should get on the bus first.</i>

315
00:23:37,280 --> 00:23:39,513
<i>Xu Huai Song isn't coming.</i>

316
00:23:39,513 --> 00:23:41,720
<i>He's probably not interested
in this kind of group activity.</i>

317
00:23:41,720 --> 00:23:44,559
<i>The summer graduation trip</i>

318
00:23:44,559 --> 00:23:46,599
<i>for Class 9 and Class 10 of Senior 3,
Grade of 2014, from Su City No.1 High School,</i>

319
00:23:46,599 --> 00:23:49,280
<i>is about to begin!</i>

320
00:23:49,280 --> 00:23:50,600
<i>Hope we can create</i>

321
00:23:50,600 --> 00:23:52,559
<i>some wonderful memories</i>

322
00:23:52,559 --> 00:23:54,279
<i>during our last group activity!</i>

323
00:23:54,279 --> 00:23:57,579
<i>Happy graduation, everyone!</i>

324
00:23:59,480 --> 00:24:00,840
<i>Fasten your seatbelts.</i>

325
00:24:00,840 --> 00:24:02,981
<i>We're ready to go!</i>

326
00:24:20,920 --> 00:24:22,880
On that trip,

327
00:24:22,880 --> 00:24:24,000
the heroine

328
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:26,670
meticulously arranged a love confession.

329
00:24:26,670 --> 00:24:28,080
But the hero

330
00:24:28,080 --> 00:24:30,340
never showed up.

331
00:24:32,519 --> 00:24:33,720
So the confession

332
00:24:33,720 --> 00:24:36,680
she had rehearsed again and again

333
00:24:36,680 --> 00:24:38,120
was destined

334
00:24:38,120 --> 00:24:40,560
never to be heard.

335
00:24:40,560 --> 00:24:43,160
And the gift she worked on without rest

336
00:24:43,160 --> 00:24:44,720
was destined

337
00:24:44,720 --> 00:24:47,126
never to be given.

338
00:24:50,079 --> 00:24:52,700
Does that sound a bit heartbreaking?

339
00:24:53,680 --> 00:24:55,273
Yes.

340
00:24:59,360 --> 00:25:01,440
But for the heroine,

341
00:25:01,440 --> 00:25:03,560
the absence of the hero

342
00:25:03,560 --> 00:25:06,846
was actually kind of an answer.

343
00:25:07,600 --> 00:25:10,146
This should be a happy ending.

344
00:25:14,839 --> 00:25:16,360
How so?

345
00:25:16,360 --> 00:25:18,400
In this world,

346
00:25:18,400 --> 00:25:20,319
the hardest thing to heal from

347
00:25:20,319 --> 00:25:22,360
is never a breakup,

348
00:25:22,360 --> 00:25:24,560
but an unrequited crush.

349
00:25:24,560 --> 00:25:26,640
Because if you've never been

350
00:25:26,640 --> 00:25:28,633
turned down,

351
00:25:28,633 --> 00:25:30,160
you can keep dreaming about

352
00:25:30,160 --> 00:25:33,400
all the ways it might've worked out.

353
00:25:33,400 --> 00:25:34,920
So,

354
00:25:34,920 --> 00:25:37,200
you end up trapped in your own fantasy forever.

355
00:25:37,200 --> 00:25:38,960
But if you muster all your courage

356
00:25:38,960 --> 00:25:40,720
and go for it,

357
00:25:40,720 --> 00:25:42,680
only to get shot down,

358
00:25:42,680 --> 00:25:44,233
then that crush

359
00:25:44,920 --> 00:25:46,440
just turns into

360
00:25:46,440 --> 00:25:48,770
a heartbreak that can be healed.

361
00:25:48,770 --> 00:25:50,519
The world is big,

362
00:25:50,519 --> 00:25:52,960
and life is long.

363
00:25:52,960 --> 00:25:57,520
She will get over him eventually.

364
00:26:09,840 --> 00:26:10,964
Lawyer Xu,

365
00:26:10,964 --> 00:26:13,105
I think you're speeding.

366
00:26:19,333 --> 00:26:20,680
The readers

367
00:26:20,680 --> 00:26:23,520
won't accept this ending.

368
00:26:23,520 --> 00:26:25,600
Maybe.

369
00:26:26,920 --> 00:26:31,040
But the endings of some stories

370
00:26:31,040 --> 00:26:33,960
were already written from the start.

371
00:26:33,960 --> 00:26:35,826
Perhaps

372
00:26:36,480 --> 00:26:39,440
even the author can't change it either.

373
00:27:09,360 --> 00:27:10,906
Mom.

374
00:27:11,640 --> 00:27:13,320
I'm fine. I didn't get wet.

375
00:27:13,320 --> 00:27:15,740
I'm already home.

376
00:27:16,760 --> 00:27:18,120
I didn't take the high-speed train.

377
00:27:18,120 --> 00:27:21,760
I ran into a friend on the way.

378
00:27:22,920 --> 00:27:24,313
Okay.

379
00:27:24,313 --> 00:27:26,939
You and Dad should rest early.

380
00:27:26,939 --> 00:27:28,798
Good night.

381
00:27:34,480 --> 00:27:36,780
<i>Is he still here?</i>

382
00:28:04,260 --> 00:28:06,160
[Love only becomes eternal in regret.]

383
00:28:06,160 --> 00:28:10,186
<i>Love only becomes eternal in regret.</i>

384
00:28:15,000 --> 00:28:16,600
<i>Perhaps years later,</i>

385
00:28:16,600 --> 00:28:18,397
<i>she'll run into him again.</i>

386
00:28:18,397 --> 00:28:20,440
<i>But by then,</i>

387
00:28:20,440 --> 00:28:22,079
<i>that spark may have long been worn away</i>

388
00:28:22,079 --> 00:28:24,400
<i>by the grind of daily life
and the passage of time.</i>

389
00:28:24,400 --> 00:28:27,680
<i>Love only becomes eternal in regret.</i>

390
00:28:40,520 --> 00:28:45,606
[Love only becomes eternal in regret.]

391
00:28:47,000 --> 00:28:48,119
<i>Indeed.</i>

392
00:28:48,119 --> 00:28:49,677
<i>Among all the literary works in the world,</i>

393
00:28:49,677 --> 00:28:51,000
<i>it's always the tragedies</i>

394
00:28:51,000 --> 00:28:52,873
<i>that leave a deeper mark in our hearts.</i>

395
00:28:52,873 --> 00:28:56,099
<i>What's the point of changing the ending?</i>

396
00:29:14,400 --> 00:29:16,440
<i>The world is big,</i>

397
00:29:16,440 --> 00:29:18,752
<i>and life is long.</i>

398
00:29:18,752 --> 00:29:23,020
<i>She will get over him eventually.</i>

399
00:29:58,980 --> 00:30:03,420
[Still up?] [Let's talk about the case.]

400
00:30:03,420 --> 00:30:07,633
[Bring me a bowl of porridge.
New District Hospital. Room 106.]

401
00:30:10,080 --> 00:30:11,640
<i>Glutinous rice is hard to digest,</i>

402
00:30:11,640 --> 00:30:14,559
<i>so I didn't add it.</i>

403
00:30:14,559 --> 00:30:16,880
<i>The texture might be a bit off.</i>

404
00:30:16,880 --> 00:30:20,816
<i>Just make do with it.</i>

405
00:30:20,816 --> 00:30:22,293
<i>Yes.</i>

406
00:30:24,800 --> 00:30:26,960
<i>It tastes very authentic.</i>

407
00:30:37,920 --> 00:30:40,900
[I saw your email.]
[You must be tired working this late.]

408
00:30:40,900 --> 00:30:42,740
[When can we discuss the case?]
[In ten minutes.]

409
00:30:42,740 --> 00:30:45,180
[What?]
[Meet me downstairs in ten minutes.]

410
00:31:02,880 --> 00:31:04,160
<i>Lawyer Xu,</i>

411
00:31:04,160 --> 00:31:06,160
<i>I switched it to Su City lard rice cake.</i>

412
00:31:06,160 --> 00:31:07,240
<i>You've been abroad,</i>

413
00:31:07,240 --> 00:31:09,799
<i>so you probably don't get this much.</i>

414
00:31:09,799 --> 00:31:11,599
<i>Thank you.</i>

415
00:31:27,359 --> 00:31:29,160
<i>Song, have you arrived?</i>

416
00:31:29,160 --> 00:31:31,480
<i>Remember to hold the umbrella for her
when she gets out.</i>

417
00:31:31,480 --> 00:31:34,039
<i>Rainy days are the perfect time
to get closer to someone.</i>

418
00:31:34,039 --> 00:31:36,500
<i>Don't miss the chance.</i>

419
00:31:38,519 --> 00:31:41,780
What if I don't have a chance
to hold an umbrella for her anymore?

420
00:32:01,485 --> 00:32:02,760
[Editor Shen]
Don't worry.

421
00:32:02,760 --> 00:32:04,920
I won't drop the story. I promise.

422
00:32:04,920 --> 00:32:06,760
Just give me some time

423
00:32:06,760 --> 00:32:09,373
to gather my thoughts.

424
00:32:09,373 --> 00:32:10,560
Fortunately, the lawsuit

425
00:32:10,560 --> 00:32:12,240
is about to come to an end.

426
00:32:12,240 --> 00:32:14,000
What about you and Xu Huai Song?

427
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:15,840
Is that coming to an end too?

428
00:32:15,840 --> 00:32:17,755
Of course.

429
00:32:17,755 --> 00:32:19,799
After the case is over,

430
00:32:19,799 --> 00:32:23,240
he'll probably go back to the US.

431
00:32:23,240 --> 00:32:25,359
That sounds like a good thing.

432
00:32:25,359 --> 00:32:27,119
You won't have to worry about

433
00:32:27,119 --> 00:32:30,300
being unmasked or embarrassed anymore.

434
00:32:31,200 --> 00:32:33,160
Why did you sigh?

435
00:32:33,160 --> 00:32:36,800
<i>Are you reluctant to let him go?</i>

436
00:32:36,800 --> 00:32:39,166
Did I just sigh?

437
00:32:40,279 --> 00:32:42,519
Fine.

438
00:32:42,519 --> 00:32:43,760
Maybe it's because I talked to Xu Huai Song

439
00:32:43,760 --> 00:32:46,833
about the ending of my novel today.

440
00:32:48,280 --> 00:32:50,900
I guess I got a bit caught up in the sadness.

441
00:32:52,240 --> 00:32:54,720
It seems my prediction about
the rekindling flame of your past affection

442
00:32:54,720 --> 00:32:57,880
is coming true, step by step.

443
00:32:57,880 --> 00:33:00,880
It's just an old wound acting up again.

444
00:33:00,880 --> 00:33:02,759
Isn't that terrifying?

445
00:33:02,759 --> 00:33:04,119
<i>Listen, you're getting too involved</i>

446
00:33:04,119 --> 00:33:05,440
<i>in the name of art.</i>

447
00:33:05,440 --> 00:33:08,206
It's easy to get into character,
but hard to get out of it.

448
00:33:08,206 --> 00:33:09,319
Have you forgotten

449
00:33:09,319 --> 00:33:11,200
how long it took you to get over him?

450
00:33:11,200 --> 00:33:13,680
Even... even after you graduated from college,

451
00:33:13,680 --> 00:33:15,680
you still thought about him sometimes.

452
00:33:15,680 --> 00:33:17,119
<i>Now he's basically</i>

453
00:33:17,119 --> 00:33:19,160
<i>walking back into your life again,</i>

454
00:33:19,160 --> 00:33:20,760
only to walk away once more.

455
00:33:20,760 --> 00:33:23,760
Back then, I didn't even get to see him
one last time.

456
00:33:23,760 --> 00:33:26,226
That's why I couldn't move on for so long.

457
00:33:27,440 --> 00:33:29,406
This time...

458
00:33:30,119 --> 00:33:32,880
If I say a proper goodbye this time,

459
00:33:32,880 --> 00:33:34,640
I guess I'll be fine.

460
00:33:34,640 --> 00:33:36,980
What proper goodbye?

461
00:34:02,160 --> 00:34:03,759
No, wait.

462
00:34:03,759 --> 00:34:06,039
Let's take a break, please.

463
00:34:06,039 --> 00:34:07,680
What made you

464
00:34:07,680 --> 00:34:08,760
so upset?

465
00:34:08,760 --> 00:34:10,280
You're clearly taking it out on me.

466
00:34:10,280 --> 00:34:11,480
How could it be?

467
00:34:11,480 --> 00:34:13,073
I'm done.

468
00:34:20,160 --> 00:34:23,020
Is there some kind of misunderstanding
between you two?

469
00:34:24,840 --> 00:34:26,620
Misunderstanding?

470
00:34:27,920 --> 00:34:30,635
When I was in the hospital,
she brought me porridge.

471
00:34:30,635 --> 00:34:32,199
Was that a misunderstanding?

472
00:34:32,199 --> 00:34:35,000
Didn't you text her and ask her to come?

473
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:37,480
What about the fried lard rice cakes?

474
00:34:37,480 --> 00:34:40,239
Didn't you tell her you were hungry?

475
00:34:40,239 --> 00:34:41,400
Right.

476
00:34:41,400 --> 00:34:44,159
I basically begged her to do these nice things.

477
00:34:44,159 --> 00:34:46,740
It was just my wishful thinking.

478
00:34:47,840 --> 00:34:49,593
That's right.

479
00:34:51,760 --> 00:34:53,600
Maybe not.

480
00:34:54,320 --> 00:34:56,640
However...

481
00:34:56,640 --> 00:34:59,373
I've got some advice for you.

482
00:34:59,373 --> 00:35:01,640
Didn't you always tell me to stop being

483
00:35:01,640 --> 00:35:03,720
so wishful all the time?

484
00:35:03,720 --> 00:35:06,673
I've learned a lot lately.

485
00:35:08,320 --> 00:35:09,880
Look,

486
00:35:09,880 --> 00:35:11,480
stop being

487
00:35:11,480 --> 00:35:13,559
so stubborn and pessimistic.

488
00:35:13,559 --> 00:35:15,280
What's wrong with begging for candy?

489
00:35:15,280 --> 00:35:18,280
Isn't it also sweet?

490
00:35:18,280 --> 00:35:20,400
If there's candy, just eat it.

491
00:35:20,400 --> 00:35:22,120
Enjoy it when you have the chance,

492
00:35:22,120 --> 00:35:23,800
right?

493
00:35:23,800 --> 00:35:26,740
You're not entirely wrong to feel that way.

494
00:35:28,240 --> 00:35:30,119
Don't rush.

495
00:35:30,119 --> 00:35:31,480
Let's wait and see

496
00:35:31,480 --> 00:35:35,106
if she'll still give you candy

497
00:35:35,106 --> 00:35:37,859
when you stop asking for it.

498
00:35:42,440 --> 00:35:44,013
Right?

499
00:35:44,680 --> 00:35:47,773
Look, speak of the devil. She just texted.

500
00:35:51,600 --> 00:35:53,559
<i>Dear lawyers,
the trial is the day after tomorrow.</i>

501
00:35:53,559 --> 00:35:55,266
<i>Shall we meet at the court entrance?</i>

502
00:35:55,266 --> 00:35:56,559
<i>If you have time tomorrow,</i>

503
00:35:56,559 --> 00:35:57,640
<i>come by the law firm.</i>

504
00:35:57,640 --> 00:36:01,060
<i>We'll go over some of the procedural details
with you again.</i>

505
00:36:02,440 --> 00:36:06,033
Aren't you curious at all about
what she said in the group chat?

506
00:36:08,360 --> 00:36:10,733
<i>Sure. But I'm busy tomorrow morning.</i>

507
00:36:10,733 --> 00:36:13,712
<i>Lawyer Liu,
what time in the afternoon works for you?</i>

508
00:36:15,920 --> 00:36:17,239
<i>We'll have to make it early.</i>

509
00:36:17,239 --> 00:36:20,140
<i>I have an appointment later in the afternoon.</i>

510
00:36:22,480 --> 00:36:24,079
Xu Huai Song.

511
00:36:24,079 --> 00:36:27,260
Did you grow up on a diet of pure willpower?

512
00:36:28,000 --> 00:36:29,880
You're clearly dying of curiosity,

513
00:36:29,880 --> 00:36:32,040
yet you won't even take one look at your phone.

514
00:36:32,040 --> 00:36:34,640
I made it very clear from the start.

515
00:36:34,640 --> 00:36:36,080
I'll handle the case preparation,

516
00:36:36,080 --> 00:36:37,600
and you take care of the court proceedings.

517
00:36:37,600 --> 00:36:40,079
Now that my preparation work is all done,

518
00:36:40,079 --> 00:36:42,320
she is your client now.

519
00:36:44,680 --> 00:36:47,240
You've been using work as an excuse, and now

520
00:36:47,240 --> 00:36:48,903
you're pretending to keep work

521
00:36:48,903 --> 00:36:50,903
and personal life separate.

522
00:36:52,280 --> 00:36:53,480
Fine.

523
00:36:53,480 --> 00:36:55,000
Keep being stubborn.

524
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:57,260
Just don't hurt yourself.

525
00:36:59,160 --> 00:37:00,440
Tomorrow at 1:00 p.m.,

526
00:37:00,440 --> 00:37:02,560
we'll have the final pre-trial briefing
with Ruan Yu.

527
00:37:02,560 --> 00:37:05,437
This is also your last chance
to have a meeting with her.

528
00:37:05,437 --> 00:37:08,140
Don't say I didn't warn you.

529
00:37:15,400 --> 00:37:17,800
- Again?
- Keep going.

530
00:37:17,800 --> 00:37:19,480
Go easy on me then.

531
00:37:19,480 --> 00:37:21,940
Let's go a few more rounds.

532
00:37:24,506 --> 00:37:25,719
<i>We finally hit 50,000 views</i>

533
00:37:25,719 --> 00:37:27,639
<i>in a single live-streaming session.</i>

534
00:37:27,639 --> 00:37:30,100
<i>Thank you all for your help.</i>

535
00:37:33,080 --> 00:37:36,820
When are you coming back?

536
00:37:36,820 --> 00:37:40,000
[Land rover defender tough stories
durability and strength]

537
00:37:40,000 --> 00:37:42,906
[Make more of your adventure with a vehicle
designed to stand the test of time.]

538
00:37:49,560 --> 00:37:51,199
<i>Babe,</i>

539
00:37:51,199 --> 00:37:53,440
<i>why are your hands so cold?</i>

540
00:37:53,440 --> 00:37:55,360
<i>Are they?</i>

541
00:37:55,360 --> 00:37:57,459
<i>Let me warm them up for you.</i>

542
00:38:02,640 --> 00:38:05,100
[Defender 110 Defender 90]

543
00:38:08,000 --> 00:38:10,180
<i>Warm them up.</i>

544
00:38:16,840 --> 00:38:20,660
[December 25, 5th Anniversary]

545
00:38:32,800 --> 00:38:35,339
This wine smells great.

546
00:38:36,813 --> 00:38:38,600
Hello?

547
00:38:38,600 --> 00:38:40,719
Hello, Mr. Zhang Chuan.

548
00:38:40,719 --> 00:38:42,679
What's keeping you busy?

549
00:38:42,679 --> 00:38:44,800
Why haven't you replied to my messages?

550
00:38:44,800 --> 00:38:46,000
Sorry, I was a bit busy,

551
00:38:46,000 --> 00:38:47,560
and I didn't see your messages.

552
00:38:47,560 --> 00:38:50,380
It's okay. Are you done? I can pick you up.

553
00:38:50,380 --> 00:38:51,577
No, thanks.

554
00:38:51,577 --> 00:38:52,920
We're having a celebration.

555
00:38:52,920 --> 00:38:54,159
It's not appropriate.

556
00:38:54,159 --> 00:38:55,360
<i>I'll call you back later.</i>

557
00:38:56,320 --> 00:38:58,979
All right then. Get back to your business.

558
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:04,306
Why did he sound so formal?

559
00:39:05,139 --> 00:39:06,340
Zhang Chuan,

560
00:39:06,340 --> 00:39:07,480
did you see?

561
00:39:07,480 --> 00:39:09,520
That one. Right there.

562
00:39:09,520 --> 00:39:11,981
That's Mr. Gao's daughter.

563
00:39:29,559 --> 00:39:31,359
Okay.

564
00:39:33,760 --> 00:39:34,920
Ms. Gao.

565
00:39:34,920 --> 00:39:37,000
Careful!

566
00:39:46,840 --> 00:39:49,346
It's okay. Just be careful.

567
00:39:50,360 --> 00:39:52,060
I'm sorry.

568
00:39:55,240 --> 00:39:57,180
Zhang Chuan?

569
00:40:02,240 --> 00:40:03,920
You remember me, Ms. Gao?

570
00:40:03,920 --> 00:40:05,239
Of course.

571
00:40:05,239 --> 00:40:07,780
We met at the office before.

572
00:40:12,360 --> 00:40:14,199
Thank you.

573
00:40:14,199 --> 00:40:16,100
You're welcome.

574
00:40:17,400 --> 00:40:19,039
- Ms. Gao.
- How have you been?

575
00:40:19,039 --> 00:40:20,939
Pretty well.

576
00:40:45,520 --> 00:40:47,840
Ms. Gao.

577
00:40:47,840 --> 00:40:50,440
How are you getting home?

578
00:40:50,440 --> 00:40:52,700
My driver is picking me up.

579
00:40:53,920 --> 00:40:55,780
Here.

580
00:41:08,519 --> 00:41:10,979
See you next time, Ms. Gao.

581
00:41:17,200 --> 00:41:19,140
Together?

582
00:41:26,680 --> 00:41:28,620
Be safe.

583
00:41:52,239 --> 00:41:53,559
What time is it?

584
00:41:53,559 --> 00:41:56,360
Why are you working so early?

585
00:41:56,360 --> 00:41:59,113
Are you that eager to see my client?

586
00:41:59,800 --> 00:42:01,400
Weren't you acting tough yesterday?

587
00:42:01,400 --> 00:42:03,580
Have you finally figured it out?

588
00:42:04,166 --> 00:42:05,560
Well, I guess

589
00:42:05,560 --> 00:42:07,800
keeping you company last night

590
00:42:07,800 --> 00:42:10,100
wasn't all for nothing.

591
00:42:14,960 --> 00:42:17,180
What are you looking at?

592
00:42:18,440 --> 00:42:21,287
You didn't prepare
Ruan Yu's pre-trial materials?

593
00:42:21,287 --> 00:42:23,760
That's your job.

594
00:42:23,760 --> 00:42:27,000
Even if it's my job,
why are you looking at these?

595
00:42:27,000 --> 00:42:28,440
This is a divorce case from years ago.

596
00:42:28,440 --> 00:42:30,440
The client has remarried,

597
00:42:30,440 --> 00:42:31,480
and the kid is already three years old.

598
00:42:31,480 --> 00:42:33,119
Why are you still reading it?

599
00:42:33,119 --> 00:42:34,720
Just checking the filing status.

600
00:42:34,720 --> 00:42:36,689
All of these?

601
00:42:36,689 --> 00:42:38,280
Yes.

602
00:42:38,280 --> 00:42:41,220
Did you sleep at the office
after playing badminton?

603
00:42:42,640 --> 00:42:45,159
No wonder they say, "Unlucky in love,

604
00:42:45,159 --> 00:42:46,639
lucky in career."

605
00:42:46,639 --> 00:42:49,039
If you keep working like this,

606
00:42:49,039 --> 00:42:50,760
how could you not be successful?

607
00:42:50,760 --> 00:42:51,760
I think

608
00:42:51,760 --> 00:42:53,000
you just have too much energy

609
00:42:53,000 --> 00:42:55,186
with nowhere to spend it.

610
00:42:55,880 --> 00:42:58,040
The pre-trial counseling is this afternoon.

611
00:42:58,040 --> 00:43:00,539
Don't you need to prepare for it?

612
00:43:01,400 --> 00:43:02,840
Fine, then I'll just...

613
00:43:02,840 --> 00:43:06,000
thank you for working day and night

614
00:43:06,000 --> 00:43:07,564
and sacrificing your rest time

615
00:43:07,564 --> 00:43:08,880
to lighten the workload

616
00:43:08,880 --> 00:43:10,240
for everyone else at the firm.

617
00:43:10,240 --> 00:43:13,280
I was too narrow-minded.

618
00:43:13,280 --> 00:43:14,880
Goodbye.

619
00:43:16,040 --> 00:43:18,280
You've been watching too much
"In the Name of Blossom" lately, haven't you?

620
00:43:18,280 --> 00:43:20,800
That drama is actually quite good.

621
00:43:26,079 --> 00:43:27,599
Lawyer Liu.

622
00:43:27,599 --> 00:43:28,760
Is Lawyer Xu

623
00:43:28,760 --> 00:43:30,360
not attending today's meeting?

624
00:43:30,360 --> 00:43:33,200
Yes, he had to attend to another case
at the last minute.

625
00:43:33,200 --> 00:43:37,200
Don't worry.
I've already reviewed all your materials.

626
00:43:38,320 --> 00:43:39,953
It's okay.

627
00:43:43,440 --> 00:43:45,440
- Didn't you say...
- I won't have time

628
00:43:45,440 --> 00:43:46,719
for the next pre-trial counseling.

629
00:43:46,719 --> 00:43:48,700
Just this once.

630
00:43:50,320 --> 00:43:52,580
Just this once?

631
00:43:57,120 --> 00:43:58,320
Fine.

632
00:43:58,320 --> 00:44:01,180
Just this once, okay.

633
00:44:03,280 --> 00:44:06,260
But I only printed two copies of this file.

634
00:44:12,040 --> 00:44:14,740
Why don't you share one?

635
00:44:15,680 --> 00:44:17,760
No need. I'll just take a photo.

636
00:44:17,760 --> 00:44:19,480
Don't. That's so inappropriate.

637
00:44:19,480 --> 00:44:21,480
It's okay. Take this one,

638
00:44:21,480 --> 00:44:23,780
and we'll share the other copy.

639
00:44:27,000 --> 00:44:28,480
<i>You used to jump at every chance,</i>

640
00:44:28,480 --> 00:44:30,120
<i>but now you're just letting it slip away.</i>

641
00:44:30,120 --> 00:44:32,720
<i>It must've hit you really hard.</i>

642
00:44:37,040 --> 00:44:39,000
Then let's begin.

643
00:44:39,000 --> 00:44:40,920
With you two amazing lawyers,

644
00:44:40,920 --> 00:44:43,606
I believe we'll definitely win this case.

645
00:44:43,606 --> 00:44:45,280
Don't be blindly optimistic.

646
00:44:45,280 --> 00:44:47,640
Until the court issues a final judgment,

647
00:44:47,640 --> 00:44:49,520
no one can be 100 percent sure

648
00:44:49,520 --> 00:44:51,237
of a specific outcome.

649
00:44:51,237 --> 00:44:52,400
Lawyer Xu,

650
00:44:52,400 --> 00:44:55,240
could there still be
something unexpected regarding this case?

651
00:44:58,119 --> 00:44:59,159
Here's the thing.

652
00:44:59,159 --> 00:45:01,200
An ambush defense is possible,

653
00:45:01,200 --> 00:45:03,973
but the chance is very slim.

654
00:45:03,973 --> 00:45:05,320
If that really happens,

655
00:45:05,320 --> 00:45:06,320
don't worry.

656
00:45:06,320 --> 00:45:08,679
I can still handle it.

657
00:45:08,679 --> 00:45:11,320
Don't be scared by his words.

658
00:45:11,320 --> 00:45:14,373
He's been going through some things lately.

659
00:45:15,280 --> 00:45:17,640
And he's become extremely pessimistic.

660
00:45:17,640 --> 00:45:19,920
If you could cut down on the nonsense,

661
00:45:19,920 --> 00:45:22,739
I think I'd be more optimistic.

662
00:45:28,640 --> 00:45:31,020
Then let's officially begin.

663
00:45:39,360 --> 00:45:41,200
That's the general picture of your case.

664
00:45:41,200 --> 00:45:42,920
Ruan Yu, if you have

665
00:45:42,920 --> 00:45:44,640
any other questions,

666
00:45:44,640 --> 00:45:47,280
you can ask Lawyer Xu.

667
00:45:50,760 --> 00:45:52,400
No need.

668
00:45:52,400 --> 00:45:56,033
Lawyer Liu, you've already explained
everything clearly.

669
00:46:09,333 --> 00:46:11,120
I'm going back.

670
00:46:11,120 --> 00:46:13,021
Lawyer Xu.

671
00:46:16,159 --> 00:46:17,720
The rain was so heavy yesterday.

672
00:46:17,720 --> 00:46:19,304
I was in a hurry

673
00:46:19,304 --> 00:46:21,946
and didn't get to say thank you.

674
00:46:22,679 --> 00:46:25,480
Thank you for giving me a ride.

675
00:46:25,480 --> 00:46:27,599
It was on my way.

676
00:46:27,599 --> 00:46:29,499
Wait.

677
00:47:05,960 --> 00:47:08,320
<i>Happy graduation.</i>

678
00:47:08,320 --> 00:47:10,100
<i>And...</i>

679
00:47:10,985 --> 00:47:12,805
<i>goodbye.</i>

